1. Overview
The Operations Tower is a role-scoped web application backed by a FastAPI service and Supabase-managed PostgreSQL. Phase‑1 MVP centres on three AI agents — Delivery Performance, Quality Intelligence, and Client Interaction — operating on a shared operational data model.

Every workflow in this document follows four cross-cutting rules established in the project documentation:

Tenant isolation — client users never see another organisation's data; enforced by PostgreSQL RLS, not application logic alone.
Evidence-backed AI — every agent output (alert narrative, NL answer, client communication draft) must cite specific source rows via evidence-link tables.
Human-in-the-loop for outbound client communications — AI drafts; a Delivery Manager must explicitly approve before anything is sent.
Synthetic data only in non-prod — build and test environments use sanitised seed data until governance sign-off (01. Project Summary.md §6).
