4. Authentication and Session Flow
All user-facing workflows begin with Supabase Auth. The planned flow matches 05. Tech Stack.md §4.

User                Frontend                  Supabase Auth           FastAPI                 PostgreSQL (RLS)
  │                    │                           │                    │                         │
  │── login ──────────►│                           │                    │                         │
  │                    │── signInWithPassword ────►│                    │                         │
  │                    │◄── JWT (access+refresh) ─│                    │                         │
  │                    │                           │                    │                         │
  │                    │── store token ────────────│                    │                         │
  │                    │   (httpOnly cookie TBD)   │                    │                         │
  │                    │                           │                    │                         │
  │── navigate ───────►│                           │                    │                         │
  │                    │── GET /api/... ───────────────────────────────►│                         │
  │                    │   Authorization: Bearer <JWT>                  │                         │
  │                    │                           │                    │── validate JWT ────────►│
  │                    │                           │                    │── set auth.uid() ──────►│
  │                    │                           │                    │◄── RLS-filtered rows ───│
  │                    │◄── JSON response ──────────────────────────────│                         │
Role resolution: The backend resolves the caller's app_role and org_id from the users table (keyed to auth.users.id). Route handlers and RLS policies must agree — a client role must never receive another org's project_id even if the API path is guessed.

Super Admin exception: Super Admin bypasses RLS only on platform-config tables (metric_configurations), not on client operational data (05. Tech Stack.md §4 — confirm scope before implementation).

