6. User Interaction Flows
6.1 Client — project status and NL query
1. Client logs in (Supabase Auth)
2. Frontend loads projects WHERE org_id = user's org_id (RLS)
3. Dashboard renders metrics from metric_configurations (client-visible only)
4. Client views delivery_confidence_scores for current milestone
5. Client submits NL question via agent query UI
6. Frontend POST → backend agent endpoint (see 09. API Specification.md)
7. Backend:
   a. Validates JWT + role
   b. Retrieves scoped operational data (RAG — see 11. AI & RAG Architecture.md)
   c. Calls LLM with grounded context
   d. Persists agent_queries + agent_query_evidence_links
8. Frontend displays answer with expandable evidence citations
6.2 Delivery Manager — risk triage and alert resolution
1. DM logs in
2. Dashboard loads all projects for org_id
3. TanStack Query polls risk_alerts (status = 'open') and bottlenecks
4. DM opens alert detail — sees contributing_causes JSONB + linked evidence
5. DM acknowledges or resolves alert → PATCH updates status, resolved_by, resolved_at
6. Optional: notification marked is_read in notifications table
Draft quality thresholds that trigger alerts (WIP — 01. Project Summary.md §5):

Signal	Draft threshold
On-time milestone delivery	≥ 90%
Schedule confidence	≥ 80% = on track
Gold-set accuracy	≥ 95%
IAA (Krippendorff's α)	≥ 0.85
Rework rate	≤ 5%
6.3 Delivery Manager — communication approval
1. Client Interaction Agent generates weekly/executive summary (scheduled or on-demand)
2. Draft appears in DM approval queue (status = 'draft' | 'in_review')
3. DM reviews body_draft and communication_evidence_links
4. DM actions:
   ├── Approve → status = 'approved', approved_by/approved_at set
   ├── Reject  → status = 'rejected' (agent must regenerate)
   └── Edit    → body_approved populated; then approve
5. Send action → status = 'sent', sent_at set; client becomes visible via RLS
100% of outbound client communications require explicit DM approval (01. Project Summary.md §5).

6.4 Super Admin — client metric configuration
1. Super Admin opens metric configuration page
2. CRUD on metric_configurations (only role with INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE)
3. Changes take effect on next client dashboard load — no code deploy required
4. Client dashboards read is_client_visible + display_order at runtime
